-- Rumford Wins Golf’s Ballantine’s Championship With Playoff Eagle
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-04-28T13:06:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-28/rumford-wins-golf-s-ballantine-s-championship-with-playoff-eagle.html
 Australia’s Brett Rumford scored
an eagle three on the first hole of a three-way playoff to win
golf’s Ballantine’s Championship in South Korea today.  Rumford had blown a two-stroke lead with two holes left,
finishing level in regulation play with Marcus Fraser of
Australia and Scotland’s Peter Whiteford on 11-under 277 in
Seoul.  It was Rumford’s fourth win on the European Tour and he
picked up a check for 367,500 euros ($478,000).  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 